channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: House Financial Services Committee Calls for Resignation of FDIC Chairman Gruenberg
NY v. Trump: Michael Cohen testifies he's considering congressional run
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's former personal attorney Michael Cohen testified in the NY v. Trump trial that he's considering a run for Congress.

item.title: John Bolton to Newsmax: International Criminal Court Is Bad Idea
item.description: The International Criminal Court (ICC) is a fundamentally illegitimate institution, according to John Bolton, former ambassador to the United Nations, on Newsmax.

item.title: Woke Journo Sticks Foot in Mouth in Column Calling for Harrison Butker to Be Replaced With Female Kicker
Netanyahu arrest warrant called 'gift to terrorists' as pro-Israel lawmakers vow revenge
item.description: Pro-Israel lawmakers on Capitol Hill are furious at the ICC chief prosecutor's decision to seek arrest warrants against top members of the Israeli government.

item.title: Biden: ICC Arrest Warrants for Israeli Leaders 'Outrageous'
item.description: President Joe Biden on Monday slammed the International Criminal Court prosecutor's application for arrest warrants for senior Israeli officials including Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, calling the move "outrageous."

item.title: Urgent Message for Oklahomans Who Care About Voting Integrity
Biden slams ICC’s ‘outrageous’ request for Netanyahu arrest warrant
item.description: President Biden said Monday that it is "outrageous" for the International Criminal Court to pursue arrest warrants against Israeli leaders.

item.title: Sens. Cruz, Britt to Newsmax: Proposed IVF Bill Protects Parents
item.description: A new bill aiming to "unequivocally" protect in vitro fertilization should draw bipartisan support because "we all agree" protecting the ability of parents to have a child "is a wonderful thing," co-sponsors of the legislation, GOP Sens. Ted Cruz and Katie Britt said.

item.title: UK Court Ruling: Julian Assange Will Be Given a Chance to Appeal His Extradition to the US
GOP Senate candidate in crucial state rips Schumer's immigration push after border trip: 'Height of cynicism'
item.description: Pennsylvania's Republican Senate nominee, Dave McCormick, takes aim at President Biden, Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer and Democratic Sen. Bob Casey over border security.

item.title: House GOP: Immigration Bill 'Dead on Arrival'
item.description: Calling the bill "dead on arrival," House Republicans derided the Senate's attempt for a vote on bipartisan immigration legislation this week as a political ploy, Politico reported Monday.

item.title: Alvin Bragg's Case in Shambles After Michael Cohen Admits to Stealing From Trump and More
Louisiana governor poised to sign stringent transgender bathroom bill
item.description: The Louisiana state legislature passed on Friday what critics claim to be one of the most stringent transgender-related policies of any state.

item.title: Colorado Dem Gov. Polis, Lawmakers Fight Space Force Proposal
item.description: Democrat Gov. Jared Polis and most members of the Colorado's U.S. congressional delegation are fighting the Biden administration's proposal that potentially would move hundreds of the state's Air National Guard members to the U.S. Space Force.
